  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Management of the EU&apos;s Humanitarian and Civil Protection Agency (ECHO) - Financial Assurance for UK implementer&apos;s.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To set up a mechanism to deliver on DFID&#x2019;s financial assurance to NGOs that we will fund the post-Exit outcomes of all EU humanitarian, development and external action programmes delivered by UK implementers, in the event that the EU terminates funding in a no deal Exit scenario. This will prevent termination of vital programming to the world&#x2019;s poorest, and allow our world-class development organisations to continue to deliver their planned programming.</narrative>
  </description>
